pproaches-supreme-court-after-waqf-bill-clears-parliament-8086074%5C%22%3ECongress%20and%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi's%20AIMIM%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20challenge%20the%20Waqf%20Amendment%20Bill%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20the%20controversial%20legislation%20awaits%20the%20President's%20assent%20after%20clearing%20both%20Houses%20of%20the%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20legislation%20that%20seeks%20to%20amend%20the%201995%20law%20governing%20Waqf%20properties%20is%20discriminatory%20and%20targets%20Muslims%2C%20claim%20Opposition%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20amendment%20will%20reduce%20the%20religious%20autonomy%20of%20Muslims%2C%20said%20AAP%20MLA%20Amanatullah%20Khan%20in%20his%20plea%2C%20contending%20that%20the%20government's%20intervention%20undermines%20the%20rights%20of%20minorities%20to%20manage%20their%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%2C%20however%2C%20has%20maintained%20that%20the%20law%20will%20benefit%20Muslim%20women%20and%20ensure%20transparency%20in%20managing%20Waqf%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChallenging%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20Waqf%20Amendment%20Bill%2C%20Mr%20Khan%20said%20the%20legislation%20violates%20multiple%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens%2C%20including%20freedom%20of%20equality%2C%20managing%20religious%20affairs%2C%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20curtails%20the%20religious%20and%20cultural%20autonomy%20of%20Muslims%2C%20enables%20arbitrary%20executive%20interference%2C%20and%20undermines%20the%20rights%20of%20minorities%20to%20manage%20their%20religious%20and%20charitable%20institutions%2C%20according%20to%20his%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20petition%20follows%20similar%20challenges%20filed%20by%20two%20other%20opposition%20MPs%2C%20Congress's%20Mohammad%20Jawed%20and%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jawed%2C%20who%20was%20part%20of%20the%20joint%20parliamentary%20committee%20on%20the%20Waqf%20bill%2C%20said%