0to%20spend%20our%20retirement%20traveling%2C%20that%20dream%20now%20feels%20out%20of%20reach.%20%3Cp%3Elucigerma%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretired-early-genx-couple-slow-travel-career-skills-champagne-test-2025-2%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretired%20early%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%2055%20with%20modest%20plans%20to%20travel%20around%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOur%20lower%20retirement%20income%20has%20not%20gone%20far%2C%20and%20bad%20luck%20in%20the%20past%20year%20cut%20into%20our%20savings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGiven%20how%20quickly%20our%20savings%20have%20dwindled%20in%20just%20a%20year%2C%20we%20have%20nixed%20our%20plans%20to%20travel.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20always%20dreamed%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanged-retirement-plans-live-in-rv-travel-full-time-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20during%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20made%20modest%20plans%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Canadians%2C%20we%20planned%20to%20mostly%20go%20on%20road%20trips%20here%20and%20in%20the%20neighboring%20United%20States%2C%20maybe%20occasionally%20flying%20to%20places%20like%20Nashville%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-things-to-do-las-vegas-weekend-what-to-skip-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELas%20Vegas%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20retired%20in%202015%20at%2055%2C%20and%20I%20joined%20him%20in%202023%20when%20I%20turned%2055.%20That%20first%20summer%20after%20I%20retired%2C%20we%20had%20an%20amazing%20time%20going%20to%20outdoor%20concerts%2C%20car%20shows%2C%20and%20impromptu%20day%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20coming%20year%2C%20I%20expected%20us%20to%20do%20more%20of%20the%20same.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20past%20few%20months%2C%20we%20realized%20our%20retirement%20dreams%20may%20be%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232ab3c00-03d9-4858-9ab8-9f7c7fced300%5C%22%3EOur%20income%20and%20savings%20aren't%20going%20as%20far%20as%20we%20expected%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20has%20started%20receiving%20payments%20from%20his%20Canada%20Pension%20Plan%2C%20which%20we%20both%20contributed%20to%20while%20working%2C%20but%20mine%20haven't%20yet%20kicked%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20others%2C%20we%20also%20sought%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-americans-unretiring-regret-not-saving-retirement-social-security-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eways%20to%20make%20money%20during%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20a%20former%20teacher%2C%20I%20take%20substitute-teaching%20jobs%20at%20local%20schools%20and%20writing%20gigs.%20My%20husband%20also%20brings%20in%20extra%20money%20building%20hunting%20shacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fshould-i-hire-retirement-advisor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplanning%20our%20pre-retirement%20with%20financial%20advisors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20felt%20confident%20we%20could%20live%20off%20our%20savings%2C%20pension%2C%20and%20money%20from%20our%20gigs%20and%20still%20travel%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20since%20our%20home%20is%20new%20and%20paid%20off%20(in%20part%20thanks%20to%20an%20inheritance%20I%20received).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20going%20to%20budget%20for%20a%20road%20trip%20every%20year%20or%20two%20until%20our%20full%20benefits%20kicked%20in%2C%20but%20we've%20already%20spent%20half%20of%20what%20we'd%20saved%20in%20this%20past%20year%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20time%2C%20we've%20had%20four%20appliance%20breakdowns%20in%20four%20months%20in%20our%20new%20home.%20We've%20taken%20in%20our%20son's%20family%20until%20they%20rebuild%20following%20a%20devastating%20house%20fire%2C%20and%20the%20basement%20bathroom%20renovation%20to%20accommodate%20them%20also%20cost%20us%2030%25%20more%20than%20we%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20unexpected%2C%20expensive%20string%20of%20bad%20luck%20in%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time%20quickly%20made%20a%20huge%20dent%20in%20our%20savings%20that%20we%20hadn't%20accounted%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20living%20on%20what%20amounts%20to%20about%20half%20of%20my%20pre-retirement%20paycheck%20has%20been%20challenging.%20Between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-turn-local-products-trump-tariffs-mislabeling-complaints-surge-fraud-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20inflation%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20many%20essentials%2C%20like%20food%2C%20are%20still%20higher%20than%20we%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20rate%2C%20we%20feel%20like%20our%20savings%20would%20be%20depleted%20far%20too%20quickly%20if%20we%20worked%20travel%20into%20our%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22da7f7cd8-9098-4042-87b6-5402823ca7bf%5C%22%3EWe've%20chosen%20to%20be%20grateful%20for%20what%20we%20have%20instead%20of%20relying%20on%20travel%20to%20find%20joy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorried%20about%20the%20future%2C%20we've%20shifted%20our%20dreams%20and%20put%20our%20travel%20retirement%20plans%20on%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20we%20still%20have%20some%20investments%20and%20savings%2C%20we%20don't%20feel%20financially%20comfortable%20or%20secure%20enough%20to%20dip%20into%20them%20to%20spend%20money%20on%20travel%20as%20we'd%20originally%20planned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20realization%20was%20difficult%20to%20handle.%20At%20times%2C%20it%20took%20a%20toll%20on%20our%20relationship%3A%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20make%20travel%20work%2C%20while%20my%20husband%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20could%20afford%20to%20get%20through%20the%20next%20few%20years%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20in%20the%20event%20we%20encounter%20more%20bad%20luck%20or%20costly%20health%20issues%20as%20we%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20taking%20a%20step%20back%20and%20looking%20at%20what%20is%20really%20important%2C%20we've%20finally%20found%20the%20blurry%20line%20between%20wants%20and%20needs%20and%20made%20peace%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20focused%20on%20becoming%20content%20in%20our%20home%20and%20finding%20happiness%20in%20small%2C%20local%20outings%3A%20going%20out%20to%20dinner%2C%20heading%20to%20the%20movies%2C%20driving%20around%20to%20look%20at%20Christmas%20lights%2C%20or%20even%20just%20visiting%20friends%20and%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20we%20are%20luckier%20than%20many%2C%20and%20our%20situation%20could%20be%20much%20worse.%20We%20can%20afford%20essentials%20like%20food%20and%20housing.%20We%20are%20surrounded%20by%20friends%20and%20family.%20We%20are%20healthy%2C%20safe%2C%20and%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20what%20we%20know%20now%2C%20I%20think%20we%20both%20would've%20worked%20a%20few%20more%20years%20and%20maybe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-diversification%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ediversified%20our%20investments%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20further%20ensure%20our%20financial%20security.%20Fortunately%2C%20we're%20at%20least%20mortgage-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20my%20benefits%20also%20kick%20in%20or%20if%20I%20take%20on%20another%20well-paying%20gig%20in%20the%20future%2C%20we%20may%20take%20a%20trip%20or%20two%20%E2%80%94%20but%20even%20if%20not%2C%20I%20have%20accepted%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20solace%20in%20feeling%20gratitude%20for%20all%20that%20we%20have%20rather%20than%20envy%20for%20the%20things%20we%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplanned-to-spend-retirement-traveling-cant-afford-it-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743857761000%2C%22visual%