%20daughters%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20their%20schools%3F%20Could%20I%20continue%20to%20pay%20the%20mortgage%20on%20our%20home%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20my%20husband%20accepted%20his%20first%20overseas%20diplomatic%20assignment%2C%20I%20gave%20up%20my%20career.%20Once%20back%20in%20the%20States%2C%20I%20began%20to%20slowly%20rebuild%20my%20professional%20life%2C%20but%20I%20was%20far%20behind%20my%20peers%20in%20earning%20power%20and%20savings.%20Still%2C%20I%20didn't%20worry%20too%20much%20about%20our%20income%20and%20my%20slow-growing%20403b.%20We%20weren't%20diligent%20savers%3B%20we%20had%20mortgages%2C%20car%20loans%2C%20and%20two%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenrolled-private-school-kids-in-public-school-thriving-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Echildren%20in%20private%20schools%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20We%20relied%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20Uncle%20Sam%20had%20our%20backs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2232bfcd18-62d9-4ee4-ae3c-aaa4f9026530%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EInsurance%20was%20a%20lifesaver%20for%20me%20during%20that%20time%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuddenly%2C%20with%20a%20base%20salary%20of%20%2442%2C000%20a%20year%2C%20I%20became%20responsible%20for%20my%20two%20teenage%20daughters%20and%2C%20as%20an%20only%20child%2C%20my%20elderly%20mom.%20My%20husband%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fhow-does-life-insurance-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egood%20life%20insurance%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20place%20(with%20his%20morbid%20sense%20of%20humor%2C%20he%20often%20joked%20about%20how%20%26quot%3Bwell%20off%26quot%3B%20I'd%20be%20when%20he%20died)%2C%20which%20was%20a%20godsend%2C%20but%20I%20needed%20to%20understand%20how%20to%20use%20our%20money%20efficiently.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMost%20financial%20experts%20say%20you%20should%20have%20enough%20money%20in%20your%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eemergency%20savings%20fund%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20cover%20three%20to%20six%20months'%20worth%20of%20living%20expenses.%20Being%20unprepared%20is%20exacerbated%20if%20you%20are%20not%20used%20to%20navigating%20the%20finances.%20In%20my%20case%2C%20I%20was%20aware%20of%20our%20position%20in%20general%20terms%2C%20but%20large%20decisions%2C%20such%20as%20our%20daughters'%20education%20and%20buying%20or%20selling%20a%20home%20or%20vehicle%2C%20were%20always%20joint.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20my%20husband's%20beneficiary%2C%20I%20received%20his%20federal%20life%20insurance%20payout.%20Early%20on%2C%20I%20received%20incorrect%20information%2C%20leading%20me%20to%20believe%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20keep%20the%20insurance%20payout%20I%20received%20in%20the%20low-interest%20settlement%20account.%20Learning%20that%20I%20was%20able%20to%20move%20it%20to%20an%20account%20that%20delivered%20a%20higher%20rate%20of%20return%20eased%20a%20lot%20of%20stress.%20My%20initial%20priority%20was%20not%20investing%20but%20making%20sure%20I%20had%20enough%20money%20coming%20in%20to%20pay%20our%20bills.%20I%20chose%20to%20work%20with%20an%20advisor%20at%20our%20credit%20union%20to%20invest%20the%20money%20in%20instruments%20that%20would%20conserve%20%E2%80%94%20and%20hopefully%20increase%20%E2%80%94%20my%20principal%20and%20provide%20an%20income%20stream%20to%20supplement%20my%20small%20salary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cb7f68bf-dff0-4d6e-a13d-36a6596ee15f%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20developed%20a%20long-term%20financial%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20advisor%20suggested%20investments%20that%20would%20help%20me%20achieve%20the%20goals%20we%20had%20planned%20for%20our%20daughters.%20I%20was%20happy%20to%20learn%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20my%20younger%20daughter%20in%20parochial%20high%20school%20and%20enable%20my%20older%20daughter%20to%20remain%20at%20her%20current%20college.%20Next%2C%20I%20paid%20off%20some%20high-interest%20items%20with%20part%20of%20the%20insurance%20money%2C%20which%20eased%20the%20burden%20on%20my%20modest%20income%20and%20saved%20me%20from%20having%20to%20make%20large%20draws%20from%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Einvestment%20accounts%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Later%2C%20I%20tackled%20estate%20planning%20issues%20such%20as%20updating%20my%20own%20will%20and%20beneficiaries%20on%20all%20financial%20items.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20though%20I%20knew%20how%20to%20access%20our%20bill-paying%20software%20and%20bank%20accounts%2C%20having%20no%20real%20savings%20of%20my%20own%20and%20a%20meager%20retirement%20plan%20due%20to%20contributions%20of%20only%20the%2010%20years%20we'd%20been%20back%20in%20the%20States%20made%20me%20anxious.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20reality%20of%20planning%20a%20possible%20solo%20retirement%20made%20me%20again%20wish%20I'd%20been%20wiser%20about%20my%20personal%20saving%20practices.%20Soon%20after%20tragedy%20strikes%2C%20many%20widows%20and%20widowers%20rush%20to%20make%20huge%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20unwise%20%E2%80%94%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20major%20financial%20decisions.%20A%20short%20time%20after%20my%20husband's%20death%2C%20I%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fshould-i-sell-my-house-now%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econsidered%20selling%20our%20home%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20but%20an%20accountant%20friend%20adv